<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-2898] Avoid initializing volatile fields to their default values</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-2898</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Contribution: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/logging-log4j2/pull/367&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/logging-log4j2/pull/367&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;From Turbanov Andrey:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s known that writing to a &lt;tt&gt;volatile&lt;/tt&gt; field has performance impact.&lt;br/&gt;
 It&apos;s true even if code initializes field with &lt;em&gt;default&lt;/em&gt; value.&lt;br/&gt;
 This PR cleans such redundant initialization and improves startup performance.&lt;br/&gt;
 See similar improvement in JDK codebase: &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.java.net/browse/JDK-8145680&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://bugs.openjdk.java.net/browse/JDK-8145680&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</description>
